.Dd December 21, 2007
.Dt OPENPAM_RESTORE_CRED 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm openpam_restore_cred
.Nd restore credentials
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libpam
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/types.h
.In security/pam_appl.h
.In security/openpam.h
.Ft "int"
.Fn openpam_restore_cred "pam_handle_t *pamh"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
function restores the credentials saved by
.Xr openpam_borrow_cred 3 .
.Pp
.Sh RETURN VALUES
The
.Nm
function returns one of the following values:
.Bl -tag -width 18n
.It Bq Er PAM_NO_MODULE_DATA
Module data not found.
.It Bq Er PAM_SYSTEM_ERR
System error.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr setegid 2 ,
.Xr seteuid 2 ,
.Xr setgroups 2 ,
.Xr openpam_borrow_cred 3 ,
.Xr pam 3 ,
.Xr pam_strerror 3
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Nm
function is an OpenPAM extension.
